                                                <div class="card-body">
                                                    <div class="instruction">
                                                        <div class="instruction-section">
                                                            <h5>Warning</h5>
                                                            <div class="instruction-inner-section">
                                                                Increased Mortality in Elderly Patients with
                                                                Dementia-Related Psychosis Elderly patients with
                                                                dementia-related psychosis treated with antipsychotic
                                                                drugs are at an increased risk of death. RisperiDONE is
                                                                not approved for the treatment of patients with
                                                                dementia-related psychosis and has not been studied in
                                                                this population.
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <ul>
                                                        <li>Beers Criteria: Avoid use for behavioral problems of
                                                            dementia and delirium (unless non-pharmacological measure
                                                            fails and the patient is a threat to self or others) due to
                                                            increased risk for cerebrovascular
                                                            accident and mortality.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Avoid use in patients with Parkinson disease, a history of
                                                            falls, fractures, or cognitive impairment as ataxia,
                                                            syncope, impaired psychomotor performance, and adverse CNS
                                                            effects may occur.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Avoid concomitant use of 3 or more CNS-active agents in any
                                                            combination due to increased risk of falls. If prescribed,
                                                            use with caution in elderly as SIADH or hyponatremia may be
                                                            exacerbated
                                                            or may occur; monitoring recommended when starting or
                                                            changing doses. May be required to treat concurrent
                                                            schizophrenia, bipolar disorder, and other selected mental
                                                            health conditions but
                                                            should be prescribed in the lowest effective dose and
                                                            shortest possible duration.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Access: While co-administration between medication-assisted
                                                            treatment (MAT) drugs (eg, methadone and buprenorphine) and
                                                            benzodiazepines or other CNS depressants (including alcohol)
                                                            may increase
                                                            the possibility of harm, including overdose and death,
                                                            concomitant therapy with MAT may be appropriate in some
                                                            patients; if concomitant use is necessary, careful
                                                            management and monitoring
                                                            recommended.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Cardiovascular: Use caution in patients with cardiovascular
                                                            or cerebrovascular disease or conditions that predispose to
                                                            hypotension, including dehydration, hypovolemia, and
                                                            antihypertensive medications
                                                            because of increased risk of orthostatic hypotension;
                                                            monitoring recommended in these patients
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Endocrine and metabolic: Patients with diabetes mellitus or
                                                            risk factors for diabetes mellitus, including obesity and
                                                            family history, are at increased risk of worsening of
                                                            glucose control or
                                                            severe hyperglycemia; monitoring recommended.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Endocrine and metabolic: Hyperglycemia, with some extreme
                                                            cases associated with ketoacidosis, hyperosmolar coma, or
                                                            death, has been reported with atypical antipsychotic use;
                                                            monitoring recommended.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Endocrine and metabolic: Hyperprolactinemia may occur and
                                                            may result in galactorrhea, amenorrhea, and gynecomastia,
                                                            and patients with longstanding hyperprolactinemia may
                                                            experience impotence,
                                                            hypogonadism, and decreased bone density; incidence of
                                                            hyperprolactinemia appears to be higher with risperiDONE
                                                            relative to other antipsychotic agents.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Endocrine and metabolic: Dyslipidemia and weight gain,
                                                            which may increase cardiovascular or cerebrovascular risk,
                                                            have been reported.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Endocrine and metabolic: Use caution in patients with
                                                            conditions that may contribute to elevated body temperature
                                                            since disruption of body temperature regulation has been
                                                            reported with antipsychotic
                                                            agents.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Endocrine and metabolic: Hyperthermia and hypothermia have
                                                            been reported; use caution in patients who will be exposed
                                                            to temperature extremes
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Falls: Falls that may lead to fracture or other injuries
                                                            may occur as a result of somnolence, postural hypotension,
                                                            or motor or sensory instability. Assessment of risk of a
                                                            fall recommended.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Gastrointestinal: Esophageal dysmotility resulting in
                                                            aspiration may occur; use cautiously in patients at risk for
                                                            aspiration pneumonia.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Hematologic: Agranulocytosis, leukopenia, and neutropenia
                                                            have been reported, especially with preexisting low WBC and
                                                            history of drug-induced leukopenia or neutropenia;
                                                            monitoring recommended
                                                            and discontinue if significant WBC decline with no other
                                                            causative factors or if patient has severe neutropenia (ie,
                                                            absolute neutrophil count less than 1000/mm(3)).
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Hepatic: Use caution in patients with hepatic impairment
                                                            since increase in the free fraction of risperiDONE reported
                                                            with severe impairment; dosage adjustment recommended.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Hepatic: Patients with hepatic impairment at an increased
                                                            risk of orthostatic hypotension; monitoring recommended
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Musculoskeletal: Potentially irreversible tardive
                                                            dyskinesia may occur and risk increases with increased
                                                            duration of therapy or higher total cumulative dose;
                                                            discontinue if appropriate.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Neurologic: Neuroleptic malignant syndrome has been
                                                            reported in association with antipsychotic drugs;
                                                            immediately discontinue if suspected.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Neurologic: Patients with Parkinson disease or dementia
                                                            with Lewy bodies are at increased sensitivity to
                                                            antipsychotic medications.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Neurologic: Use caution in patients with history of seizure
                                                            disorder or conditions that lower seizure threshold.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Renal: Use caution in patients with renal impairment since
                                                            increased plasma concentrations reported with severe
                                                            impairment (CrCl less than 30 mL/min/1.73 m(2)); dosage
                                                            adjustment recommended.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Renal: Patients with renal impairment at an increased risk
                                                            of orthostatic hypotension; monitoring recommended
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Reproductive: Priapism has been reported and severe cases
                                                            may require surgical intervention.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Special populations: Use caution in patients with
                                                            phenylketonuria as oral disintegrating tablet contains
                                                            phenylalanine, a component of aspartame.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Special populations: Elderly patients, especially elderly
                                                            women, are at increased risk of tardive dyskinesia.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Special populations: Elderly patients are at increased risk
                                                            of orthostatic hypotension, especially during the initial
                                                            dose-titration period with oral administration; monitoring
                                                            recommended.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li> Special populations: Cerebrovascular adverse events (eg,
                                                            stroke, transient ischemic attack) including fatalities have
                                                            been reported with oral risperiDONE in elderly patients with
                                                            dementia-related
                                                            psychosis (unapproved use)</li>
                                                    </ul>
