                                            hypovolemia, diabetes mellitus, or chronic hypertension; dosage
                                            reduction or interruption may be necessary. Use caution with advanced
                                            heart block or severe ventricular dysfunction. Transient hypertension
                                            has been reported, primarily during the loading dose; reduced loading
                                            infusion rate may be necessary.<br>
                                            <b>Hepatic:</b> Hepatic impairment; dosage adjustment may be necessary.<br>
                                            <b>Neurologic:</b> Arousability and alertness when stimulated
